ErlaNGinE

The Erlang, Web and CouchDB experimental concept

INSTALLATION INSTRUCTIONS

* Install git.

For Debian-based linux: apt-get install git-core
For others see http://github.com/guides/home

* Install apache CouchDB.

Follow http://couchdb.apache.org/
Run CouchDb on localhost

* Obtain sources:

git clone git://github.com/dmi/erlangine.git

* Compile

cd erlangine
make

* Init

./start-dev.sh
enge2:prepare_db().
q().

* Run

./start-dev.sh

* Try

- Point your browser to http://localhost:8080
- Register an account (Internet access to http://captchas.net required)
- Log in
- Create document
- Try search

It's all for now ;-)
